The abductors of 82-year-old mother of a business man and owner of Shema Petroleum filling stations, have demanded a ransom of N200 million for her release. The woman, Hajiya Hassana popularly known as Hajiya Diya, was abducted from her matrimonial home at about 1.30 am on Thursday by gunmen who stormed the residence, beating up other residents before whisking her away on a motorcycle. Sources close to the family told our correspondent that the abductors contacted her son, Nagogo Mammam Nagarhi. It would be recalled that during the abduction, the victimâ€™s husband, Alhaji Abdullahi was injured and is presently on admission in a hospital just as a neighbour, Usman Barkiya, was shot twice as he attempted to assist the victim. 